### Privacy Policy for data not collected from the data subject (of information directed to the public in accordance with Art. 14 para. 5 point (b) sentence 2 GDPR)

We draw the public's attention to the fact that registered users of the Data4Life web app may store data relating to third parties (details related to an emergency contact, name/speciality of healthcare professionals) in encrypted form when using the web app's functionalities. Due to the encryption of the data within our platform, we cannot at any time identify these third parties or assign the data to a natural person. Therefore, the provision of information for data that was not collected directly from the data subject pursuant to Art. 14 para. 1 - 4 GDPR  proves impossible for us in accordance with Art. 14 para. 5 point (b) sentence 1 GDPR. In order to fulfil our obligations, we therefore make the following information available to the public.

###1. Controller and data protection officer

The controller pursuant to Art. 4 para. 7 GDPR for the web app is: 

D4L data4life gGmbH
Charlottenstraße 109
14467 Potsdam
Germany

Email: we@data4life.care

You can reach our data protection officer at dataprivacy@data4life.care or our postal address by writing to the attention of "The data protection officer".

###2. Purpose of processing, source of the data, protection of your legitimate interests

Users of the Data4Life web app can optionally enter and store data concerning third parties via our web app when using the functionalities made available to the users. This refers specifically to the following data from third parties:

Information about contact persons: Users of the Data4Life web app can create an end-to-end encrypted personal health profile, which the user can share, for example, with his doctors or hospitals. Within the scope of the personal health profile the user can optionally enter details (for example, name, telephone number) of a contact person, who, for example, shall be contacted in case of a medical emergency of the user.

Information on third parties in medical documents: Users of the Data4Life web app can store and manage their medical documents (for example, findings, medical reports) securely using end-to-end encryption in the web app and to share them, for example, with other treating doctors/hospitals, which then can provide the user with more efficient treatments and healthcare services. The medical documents that the user uploaded himself can contain personal Information about third parties, for example, names, addresses, specializations of treating doctors. 

The legal basis for the processing of the aforementioned data is the legitimate interest of our web app user in accordance with Art. 6 para 1 subpara 1 point (f) GDPR to archive, store and share medical documents relating to him as easily, efficiently and securely as possible.

We ensure the protection of the rights and freedoms and the legitimate interests of the third parties concerned by means of our end-to-end encryption, which means that at no time we can obtain any knowledge of your person or access data that our user stores with us. 

###3. Recipients, categories of recipients

We do not disclose/transmit your data to third parties. Only the Data4Life user himself can share uploaded/stored and selected data/documents and his health profile on the Data4Life platform with others, for example, his doctor(s), if he so wishes. 

###4. Storage duration and deletion of data

We ourselves have no influence on how long our users store data and documents in the Data4Life web app, as this depends solely on the user and his use of the Data4Life functionalities in the web app. In principle, however, the data remains stored as long as the Data4Life user has a user account or as long as a registered user does not delete or edit his uploaded documents or his health profile at Smart4Health himself.

###5. Your rights

As a data subject in general you have the following rights regarding personal data concerning you: 
- Right to access (Art. 15 GDPR) 
- Right to rectification (Art. 16 GDPR)
- Right to erasure (Art. 17 GDPR)
- Right to restriction of processing (Art. 18 GDPR)
- Right to object to the processing (Art. 21 GDPR) 
- Right to data transferability (Art. 20 GDPR)

You also have the right to complain about our processing of your personal data to a data protection supervisory authority in the member state where you are located, at your place of work or at the location of the alleged infringement. The supervisory authority responsible for us is: 

Die Landesbeauftragte für den Datenschutz und für das Recht auf Akteneinsicht
Stahnsdorfer Damm 77
14532 Kleinmachnow 
Germany

Telephone: 0049 (0)33203/356-0
Telefax: 0049 (0)33203/356-49
Email: Poststelle@LDA.Brandenburg.de

Please note, that due to the encryption measures described in section 2 above, it is not possible for us to identify you and, due to lack of access to the documents stored by our user, we do not have and therefore cannot obtain knowledge of whether information on your person is actually stored by us. In accordance with Art. 11 para. 1 GDPR, we are not obliged to maintain, acquire or process additional information in order to identify the data subject for the sole purpose of complying  with the GDPR, insofar as the identification of the data subject, as is the case with the Data4Life web app, is not necessary for the purposes for which a controller processes personal data.
